choices.text:
Harmony used discarded paper to make notepads for her friends. She would fold five letter size pieces of paper three times then cut along the lines. She would then stack the smaller note papers and staple them together. How long would one notepad last if someone wrote ten notes per day?
If Harmony used 5 sheets of paper to make each notepad, and each sheet was folded into thirds (3 layers), then there are 5 x 3 = 15 pages in total. If someone writes 10 notes per day on these notepads, they will use 10 days / note pad = 10 notepads.

So, one of Harmony's notepads would last for:

10 notepads x 15 pages / notepad = 150 pages

Therefore, if someone writes ten notes per day on these notepads, they will be able to use them for a total of 150 days (or 4.2 months) before they run out of paper.
